                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.94.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-11-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 29, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>You may inform the Japanese Minister that commanders of United States war vessels
                    have been instructed to give protection to foreigners at ports where vessels may
                    be located. This of course includes Japanese subjects.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
